        [
          "You're a fighter, you don't give up. Which is why Justicar Theo Bell has you in his pocket.",
          "",
          "",
          "",
          "",
          "",
          "",
          "",
          "LAB"
        ],
        [
          "Staff Generated History"
        ],
        [
          "You were were born in Baltimore during the Vietnam war. Your father died overseas fighting, and your mother was barely making ends meet in one of the rougher neighborhoods. You grew up on the streets, mostly raising yourself. The early 60's were a time of great racial and social change, and you were in the thick of it: you and your gang of other discontented youths, protesting the racial segregation endemic in Baltimore. One particular protest got rough, and you barely escaped being beaten to death by a cop with a grudge.  You were found, clinging to what life you had, by one of the more outcast of your group; someone you knew, you trusted, but that kept to themselves. So you couldn't have known they were a vampire. Seeing in you the promise of a great fighter for the cause, he embraced you into a world constantly at war. He himself was a Camarilla Brujah, infiltrating the Sabbat held city of Baltimore, and brought you into his \"pack\", made up of other infiltrators pretending to be members of the Sabbat. You had no idea what you were walking into, but you went along with it, and you learned from the others, both about the sect you were nominally serving and the sect you were pretending to be. Horrified by the inhumanity on display, you felt yourself sliding further and further into depravity. Your sire didn't realize what was happening until it was almost too late. He, too, was shocked at what was happening, and sent you to stay with his superior - the Justicar, Theo Bell. Bell recognized the marks of the Beast on your soul, and gave you the space and support to make yourself whole again. At first you thought he was doing it out of brotherhood, but you've slowly come to realize that even Theo Bell has his own ulterior motives. Having once tasted the darkness and come back, Bell's confident you can resist the slide again. Is that why he's sending you to Los Angeles?"
        ],
